# REDnet CI lint policy. We enforce up to the `safety` profile (file permissions, command safety,
# parser/runtime correctness) — currently clean. The stricter `shared`/`production` idiom rules are
# deliberately NOT enforced here, with rationale:
#   no-changed-when : setup.sh and `docker compose up` are deploy actions that DO change state every run;
#                     a fake `changed_when` would be dishonest noise.
#   no-handler      : the inline "restart docker when _daemonjson.changed" is correct for this linear,
#                     two-play deploy — a handler adds indirection without benefit at this size.
profile: safety
